title: NHS to take over state-of-the-art hospital from private health group in ‘windfall’
summary: Nuffield Health is set to close its hospital in London due to lower-than-expected demand for private healthcare services. The decision reflects a shift in patient preferences and market conditions. The closure will affect staff and patients as the facility winds down operations.

title: Meet gen X: middle-aged, enraged and radicalised by internet bile | Gaby Hinsliff
summary: In her column, Gaby Hinsliff argues that the surge of populism is largely fueled by her generation, rather than the common stereotypes of angry pensioners or disenfranchised youth. She emphasizes that many in her demographic feel disillusioned and are seeking change in the political landscape. Hinsliff's insights challenge traditional perceptions of who is behind the populist movements.
